was the hardest part of the Aggie band halftime to 
prepare for? I think putting the music with the

00:26.314 --> 00:29.717
drill. In other words, you learn the drill, And 
you've got everything. You count the number of

00:34.436 --> 00:37.140
steps in the drill. Then you count the number of 
measures in the music. And you get everything all

00:39.984 --> 00:42.407
set for the grand finale. And then this means that 
you have to cut some of the music off. And getting

00:47.253 --> 00:51.798
everybody to cut it off at exactly the same time so 
it will fit the music. I think that was probably the

00:51.839 --> 00:54.542
hardest part. And like I say, Wednesday was a bad 
day because it took so many times to go over it until

00:54.742 --> 01:02.472
they... they got it and probably half as many times 
as it would have taken any other group but even as

01:03.042 --> 01:27.177
smart and determined and dedicated as these guys 
were we still had some trouble with that but after

01:03.042 --> 01:27.177
usually after about Thursday or Friday then you 
see it all fit in together and by Friday and then

01:03.042 --> 01:27.177
Saturday morning it was usually they would just 
something about that audience and getting the 50

01:27.477 --> 01:55.172
60 000 people whatever we have and getting them all 
together they just really outdid themselves all

