02:13.799 --> 02:23.335
playing the cadence and they're walking up and 
down practicing their counter marches. The drum

02:23.835 --> 02:29.805
majors are usually down on the goal line or 
somewhere, there's some part of the drill that

02:23.835 --> 02:29.805
they're just not quite sure about. They're over 
there working on that. At 7 o'clock we take a break

02:32.509 --> 02:36.917
and we go through the drill sometime. If they do it 
real good, we go through it twice. at 7. If it's not

02:40.606 --> 02:43.310
real good, we stay sometime until 7.45. But if it's 
some of the cross through sometime would give us

02:43.770 --> 02:47.515
trouble. But then usually after we get through 
with that, well then we depart and we go. They'll

02:55.425 --> 03:01.933
have on their fatigues and they'll go get on their 
uniforms and we get ready to go. But now you know

03:01.953 --> 03:03.936
they have the march in over there. That would begin 
about two hours before the game started. I had to be

03:07.991 --> 03:10.097
there so I could meet them. Then we'd have them, 
we'd have the march in and then we'd have the

03:10.678 --> 03:17.316
pregame and then we'd have the game. So you're 
talking say the game started two o'clock you're

