folks. Didn't have any black folks? No, no. Any 
international band members? We had some from

25:09.217 --> 25:11.842
Panama. Really? And we would get several of those 
every year from some country. I had one from

25:17.423 --> 25:21.909
Iroquois maybe? Do you remember, you said there 
was no black member of the band when you came? No.

25:29.159 --> 25:32.503
But after that we had- When do you remember? Can you 
describe how that worked? Well, we had probably,

25:36.089 --> 25:48.209
you know, every year we took some if they signed up, 
but I don't remember when we had the first one. Do

25:48.229 --> 25:53.097
you remember any difficulties, any incidents at 
all? No. Oh, no. No, we never had any. One of them,

25:56.142 --> 26:02.475
the last year I was there we had a black drum major. 
And he was killed about two weeks ago, or about two

26:04.038 --> 26:11.333
months ago, a month ago, in a plane crash. He had 
applied for a commission and I wrote several

26:11.313 --> 26:29.946
letters from him and he got the commission but then 
they wouldn't let him fly because of some kind of

26:11.313 --> 26:29.946
eye problem or something and then he was flying for 
the Civil Air Patrol and his plane crashed. See, I

26:30.415 --> 26:37.263
believe that this school's record on black-white 
relations has always been splendid. Oh, I think

26:37.283 --> 26:38.184
it's wonderful. We never had a menish problem. I 
tell people, as an observer, that I have the

26:40.446 --> 26:50.698
impression the key thing was not who your parents 
were, but are you an Aggie or you're not an Aggie?

26:50.718 --> 26:50.938
Absolutely. It doesn't make any difference about 
that other. Not to me, it doesn't. All right, now

26:54.021 --> 26:59.207
let's go to the admission of women in the band. When 
did anybody first contact you about? Well do you

27:04.375 --> 27:06.798
remember the Zentgraft deal? Yes I do. Do you 
remember the Zentgraft? Originally she was

27:09.382 --> 27:21.239
challenging the Color Guard and she was 
challenging the Ross Volunteers as the

27:09.382 --> 27:21.239
organization. She was not in the band. So she just 
threw in the ban as an afterthought. And then she

27:26.688 --> 27:30.735
entered that into her deal because we didn't have 
any. So did she ever come to talk to you about doing

27:31.456 --> 27:35.282
the ban? No, she never even been in the ban hall. I 
wonder if she even was a... She was upset because

27:39.249 --> 27:45.279
they wouldn't take her in the color guard, I 
believe. And so anyway, then when they went to the

27:45.299 --> 27:49.326
judge, And we were interviewed by, I could see the 
writing on the wall, just to be perfectly honest

27:49.627 --> 27:55.364
with you. And I told them the first day, I said, hey, 
we're not gonna win this. Why don't we just go ahead

27:59.737 --> 28:01.442
and do it? And let us have the $200,000 you're going 
to spend on this thing, and we'll buy something we

28:01.844 --> 28:08.711
really need with it. Oh, no, no, no, we've got to 
fight. Well, anyway, this went on for five years.

28:13.496 --> 28:28.172
And people would, and I said, hey, look, do you 
think for a minute now in Washington, D.C., they

28:13.496 --> 28:28.172
can say, they have such a good band, let's just 
leave it all male because they'll be the only one

28:13.496 --> 28:28.172
then that doesn't have it. It's not going to work 
that way. And then I didn't say anymore. But

28:32.538 --> 28:36.884
anyway, it was quite hush-hush, and I was not 
allowed to talk about it. And I said, if you'll just

28:37.945 --> 28:43.433
let us do it, we'll do it in no time. But we had a press 
conference over there. There was a

28:46.117 --> 28:54.769
representative from every major radio station 
and TV station in the country, and we took five of

28:46.117 --> 28:54.769
them in. And... And what year was that? I'm not real 
sure. I think it was Haskell, I'm not real sure. It

29:06.103 --> 29:07.744
may be in that book over there. It was in the 80s. I 
think it was in the 85 or 80s, somewhere along in

29:09.406 --> 29:13.670
there. And the first one that came in there was a 
girl about 6'2", and she was an all-state trombone

29:14.430 --> 29:30.165
player, and she was an athlete, very nice looking. 
And she still writes me. And she was the first one,

29:33.728 --> 29:38.172
she was the only one there, she was the first one to 
graduate. Now, within the typical band member,

29:39.573 --> 29:45.039
how did they react? They were all going to quit. And 
this presented a problem. And they came in and

29:51.164 --> 29:53.567
said, we're not going to stay, we're going to quit. 
I said, now, wait a minute. So I talked to John,

29:54.848 --> 29:57.470
Johnny and I talked about it a lot. John Colas. John 
Colas. And I said, Johnny, I want to find out one

29:59.312 --> 30:03.516
thing from you right quick before we go on here now. 
If they all quit like they say they are, which I

30:04.171 --> 30:10.001
think we can handle that, are we still going to have 
a ban? He said, we will have a ban if they quit. So I go

30:12.725 --> 30:17.813
back to him and I say, now, gentlemen, I want to tell 
you something. If you all quit, and boy, I mean they

30:17.833 --> 30:21.299
were 100%. If you quit like you say they are, then 
the Aggie ban is through. It's done. It's

30:29.732 --> 30:31.433
finished. Now, if you want to continue to have the 
Aggie Band with a few exceptions, you'll stay. But

30:41.324 --> 30:51.795
I have talked to the Vice President of Student 
Services, and he very confidently told me that

30:41.324 --> 30:51.795
they will have a band here whether you quit or not. 
Now, I'm asking you not to quit. Don't let four or

30:58.800 --> 31:03.726
five women ruin this organization. Said girls 
have been, said, I don't want girls in this band,

31:04.567 --> 31:11.256
but I love girls. I've been married to one for 42 
years. And they are not going to hurt us like you

31:14.300 --> 31:19.707
think they will. Well, they didn't say anything. 
Just looked and stared, glassy. So they came back,

31:24.606 --> 31:25.908
C.O. came back and said, sir, we're going to try it. 
I said, that's fine, because they're going to have

31:29.192 --> 31:37.965
a band, and I'm going to stay here, and I can go 
somewhere else or whatever, but I'm going to stay.

31:37.945 --> 31:40.553
And I think we ought to stay and do it. And they will 
wear the same things that you wear. They will have

31:45.087 --> 31:46.391
their hair. That was the main thing they were 
concerned about. They wanted them to look.

